Package edu.ucsb.cs56.pconrad.parsing.syntax

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AST
    Interface which all AST nodes must implement.
    ASTFactory
    Decouples token constructors and underlying class hierarchy from how AST nodes behave.
    ASTVisitor<A,T extends Throwable>
    Interface which visitors of ASTs must implement, as per the Visitor pattern.
    Operator
    Represents an operation, like addition (+) or multiplication (*).
    OperatorVisitor<A,T extends Throwable>
    Interface which visitors of operators must implement, as per th Visitor pattern.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Binop
    Represents binary operations, e.g., 1+2, 5*7, and so on.
    DefaultASTFactory
    Default implementation of the ASTFactory interface.
    Div
    Represents the division operation (/)
    Literal
    Represents a literal in the AST, which are simply integers for our case.
    Minus
    Represents the subtraction operation (-)
    OperatorScaffold
    Class for conveniently making operators which can be represented with a single character.
    Plus
    Represents the addition operation (+)
    Times
    Represents the multiplication operation (*)
    UnaryMinus
    Represents unary minus, e.g., -4, -10, and so on.
